caption: I am paranoid about covid so I don't go out much. But Buceo checked all the boxes. Like water carafe was left at the table so server does not keep coming near us. I love Spanish wine, Buceo has plenty on the list. With outdoor dining in winter steaming hot food is rare , and every dish we ordered was delicious  and hot. Highly recommend bacon wrapped dates. Service was excellent. I am definitely going back. And yes it is heated outdoor dining. Just one note if you don’t like salty food request less cheese and salt both. I eat extremely low salt food but with bread I found it okay.

Came here on a Tuesday for dinner with my mother who used to live in Sevilla. Mom was very satisfied. 😀 Highly recommend the gambas al ajillo, enjoyed the lamb bocadillo as well. Also pictured are the croquettes bacalao (codfish) which were a bit salty for me but my mother loved. Not pictured because we were too hungry but recommended: the goat cheese croquettes and the asparagus. Lots of great vegetarian and pescatarian options. Owner and staff were very friendly. I also got a hot toddy and my mother enjoyed a white wine.  We were content with the outside heat lamps on a cold day during the pandemic. Plenty of outside seating not too close together. Although it was a weeknight,they had several tables seated.

Ambiance was pleasant, music was too loud. The garlic shrimp left a lot to be desired, octopus was scarce and the eggplant was very salty. The highlight was their wine selection. Do not get the sangria.
Phenomenal service, solid wine and liquor selection, B+ food that everything else makes up for
A neighborhood favorite! The bacon wrapped dates, pork belly, and croquettes are favorites. They make a tasty sangria as well. Highly recommend!
Used to be 5 stars but I guess different times 🤷🏼‍♂️
Tapas and wine were great.it was nice to sit outside and be accommodated by such friendly staff.
Lovely spot, close to home, great staff, very happy. They usually have a wait for outdoor seating.
The food is good, but the portion is very small by tapas standard. The paella was particularly small. We spent ~50 per person and weren’t full at all.
Incredibly friendly owners of a warm neighborhood spot.
Delicious tapas with great options for both vegetarians and carnivores. Very large and accessible wine selection.
Never a disappointment. Somerhing for everyone. By far one of my favorite places to go to in the city

I came here for dinner. They have a really good wine list and they made good recommendations for our wine choices when we told them our flavor profile. The tapas was really good too I would highly recommend the scallops and the carne Asada. We also tried the bacon wrapped dates but those left me a little cold.  The space is smaller but they have some outdoor seating which is on the pavement, and it's got a cute look and looks authentic for a tapas bar. Bathrooms are clean and the wait staff is really good. They are busy, one can tell but they made sure our table was bussed and managed, even brought us fresh bread.

nick the host   nathan the bartender were excellent great service we stayed 5 hours  they found out it was my birthday doon and gave us pastry w chocate to dip it into   classy  great confortable beautiful place  .  we went on a sunday and had some red wines  that we learned about and will have again and again.mine was azumuti  organic  awesome thanks to buceo for making a sunday plan come to fruition
Always had to this food and amazing staff, especially the hostess and the bartender who always remembers exactly what kind of red wine I like!

The food is always superb. It is a very small place, so can someone's be difficult to get into if you're doing with a large group or at peak dinner hours. But it's a great neighborhood spot. Nice wonder selection, great flan, wonderful seasonal dishes that change. Great for sharing and tasting as many things as possible.
Amazing service, food and SANGRIA with cava!  Nathan was incredible as usual!! Thanks
Everything was delicious

Buzzy neighborhood tapas place, hidden away on 95th Street. High tabes and stools placed close together. Wide selection of interesting tapas, including some great veg options. Good selection of wines x the glass, mostly Spanish, plus sherries etc.
The Spanish cheeses are ok, I'm from Spain and I think these cheeses are not as flavor as at home. The price is high for the quantity

Visited Buceo 95 last night in search of some good tapas on the UWS – was warmly greeted upon entry and was seated almost immediately, was pleasantly surprised since the restaurant was nearly at capacity.  The wine list is long enough to accommodate anyone but, not too long as to discourage you from searching for the perfect wine and there were excellent drink options, also.  We ordered a pitcher of sangria – the flavor was excellent but, had a bit of viscosity to it that made it a little less enjoyable.  Our food order: Pan con Tomate (tomato spread on garlic bread), Alcachofas (grilled artichokes), Esparragos a la Plancha (grilled Asparagus), Pulpo de Buceo (grilled baby octopus) and a nightly special Bacon wrapped Scallops.  The food was fantastic I would recommend everything that we had, everything was cooked to perfection – loved it.  The only draw back to this location is the acoustics in the restaurant itself, went on a Tuesday night at 9pm and the restaurant was packed and very loud making it quite difficult to hold a conversation.  Regardless, I will definitely be going back.
Goggle asked me to write this.
Excellent service ,excellent food , remarcable costumer assistance..."Courtney" inbeatable....!
(Translated by Google) nice place  (Original) מקום נחמד

I don't want to give a good review of this place because it'll be more crowded and then I can't walk in and just get a table. But we're moving out of town, so I have to mention it: one of the best restaurants on the UWS. Always has a crowd even on midweek nights. Proprietor works there every night and is super friendly. And the food, oh man - have never had something less than expertly made. The goat cheese croquettes could turn my wife into a shopping cart pusher. It's definitely an adventurous menu, but really good tapas is hard to find, and other than Ella Kitchen at 71st and Columbus, this is the only really good one on the UWS .
Friendly service, a great atmosphere (outdoor seating!), and good food. However, food and drink (at least sangria) portions are very small for the prices.
No TVs... What a relief!
Good food and good wine selections!
Nice staff, good selection of wine but way too expensive. Cost me more than 50$ and still hungry.
Great food and ambience!
It's a nice place but the tapas was only ok.
Warm inviting atmosphere, good wine, food and excellent service.
(Translated by Google) It is a quiet bar ideal for someone who wants to go to talk. Low light.  (Original) Es un bar tranquilo ideal para alguien que quiere ir a conversar. Poca luz.
Wonderful wine food and service. A gem
Nice place

Great food, and a really great atmosphere. All the staff were very kind, especially the hostess who greeted us at the door. The only setback here are the prices; many of the tapas are far too expensive for the portions they give (after all, they’re tapas). I had a glass of wine and two tapas end ended up spending $55 (which, for me, is too much). But, if you have the budget, or you’d just like a great place for a date, this is a good spot.
La paella was nasty.  The place was very classy and romantic but for wasn't good.
(Translated by Google) Fabulous drops. Somewhat pricey.  (Original) Fabulous tappas. Somewhat pricey.
Excellent local wine and tapas bar.  Be sure to try the Marcona almonds
nice place, cozy with friendly staff; a bit expensive.
Food and Sangria were amazing! Must try ....awesome customer service!
Nice place love the food and so friendly people good prices service was the best
Excellent place to relax, enjoy food and great prices. A+
I come here often because not only is the food excellent but the staff adds to the warm and friendly ambience . I usually like to get waited on Kylee she is so sweet and attentive . Great spot!
Pretty small place, great atmosphere. Definitely not a dinner place. More like an after hour drink and appetizer.  The food was amazing but unfortunately spent quite a bit and was still hungry.
Great tapas, worth a visit
Excellent food and vibe. Pricey.
Food was very well prepared

Tapas are pretty small portions for their prices, but huge variety and all delicious. Great veggie options too. The wine list is extensive and high quality, and serving sizes are hefty... Staff / owner are super friendly as well, definitely a great neighborhood spot. Pretty crowded on both weeknights and weekends, but outdoor seating during the warmer months helps a bit.

Good food at a place with great atmosphere and food. The Garlic Shrimp are very good, and the prices for a tapas restaurant are mostly affordable. Biggest complaint is regarding the sangria, which they thicken (so if you're not a fan of thicker sangria, don't order it). Outside seating was nice, but the angle of the road/sidewalk makes things odd.
Dropped in with 4 others (3 of us had just finished s run-no problem) seated immediately in busy restaurant, hit or miss with dishes, not a great place for vegans but waitress very attentive.
Delicious food but a little small on the portions! Lovely sidewalk dining with great service! Would definitely go back if I'm back in the upper west side
Not cheap, but VERY nice
Great appetizers anything you eat there it's delicious
Excellent food and great service when the place was wall to wall with customers
The food is so good... but the wine prices have gotten out of hand.  Wine used to be $20-40 per bottle.  Now it's $40-70!!!

Food was good, but small portions.  The reason for 2 stars is my waiter was a complete jerk the entire time I was there.  I've worked in the service industry, I'm always kind to wait staff.  He was straight up rude to my friends and I from the moment we arrived.  I ordered a dish that was 12 dollars on the menu.  We got the bill and it was 14.  No one was coming by to grab the check for a good 20 minutes, so I ended up forgetting/giving up on asking my waiter about it.  As I was leaving, I managed to pull him over, and mentioned that the dish was incorrectly marked, just for future reference. He said nothing to me. Went over and checked the menu posted at the door (which also said 12), checked another menu inside. Came back and simply said, "no it's 14."  After looking at 2 menus that clearly said 12.  I pointed at the menu item and the 'twelve' that was next to it.  He said "... okay" and made zero effort to fix the problem.  I left angry and compelled to let people know just how rude this guy was to me and my friends.

One of our favorite Tapas places in the city. We always hear there is going to be a line, but somehow our little outside corner table in the back always opens up without a wait. The dishes are excellent and genuine. Last time I ordered Paella which was outstanding - better than we had in Spain.
Great tapas and good atmosphere. Tip: it's better to buy a bottle of wine than by the glass.
My absolute favorite Spanish tapas spot in all of NYC. Great restaurant that combines aspects of spectacular food, service, and relaxing atmosphere.
Excellent Wines and Tapas.  Very friendly and informed staff!

We had a great time at Buceo. Started with drinks and were convinced to cancel dinner reservations elsewhere. Bartender suggested awesome tapas...potato chips, shrimp, stuffed mushrooms, scallops and brussel sprouts. Delicious, friendly atmosphere and excellent food. We will be back
Really chill atmosphere and staff recommended wines are great!
Food here is very good, so is the atmosphere
Excellent Tapas. Just excellent.
Great tapas!
Super charming tapas place with great dishes and very nice wine.
(Translated by Google) Great neighborhood spot from dropping  (Original) Great neighborhood spot fr tappas
Great tapas bar,  never disappoints.
Buceo 95 is always busy, but very ambient with excellent food.  Janey tended to us and was friendly and knowledgeable with just the right degree of attentiveness.

Love this tapas place. Never had anything less than a wonderful time here. The food is delicious, the wine selection is great, both red and white. The cocktails and Sangria are delicious. A must for a Date night!
Pretty good. Pricey

Buceo has a nice vibe and I've had some great bartenders there. I haven't sampled the food, but the drinks are good. I do wish there were some other scotches and beers to choose from (but that's just based on what I like to drink).
FAVORITE Spanish tapas!!!!!  Staff always friendly and accommodating!!!!!  Bar tender makes the best Nigronis and other cocktails!!!!!

Very popular tapas restaurant in the Upper West Side.  The staff was very nice and friendly.  The tapas my wife and I tried were generally good although a bit overpriced.  The place was quite loud and packed when we went.  The atmosphere was cozy and dim.  Of the dishes we tried...the Patatas Freitas I ordered was probably the most disappointing.....it literally was $6 potato chips....I guess I was expecting more there.  The Coliflor a la Brasa was delicious and highly recommended.  Overall, I recommend coming and trying this restaurant out for yourself.
Thus is my go to neighborhood bar,great tapas excellent service

Great place for dinner and a couple of drinks, especially if solo. It's usually possible to get a spot at the bar, where you'll likely find the staff and locals to be friendly and chatty. Did I mention that the food, drinks and staff are all excellent?
Really good for snacks. Must try "Churrasco" Yummy!

Honestly just mediocrity incarnate. Could write a long detailed review but that just sums it up. If this place figures out its service (waited almost 30 minutes just to get the check) it may deserve and extra star or two but why bother given the tiny portions of bland food (cauliflower came in a soy sauce sized dish and cost $15). Just skip

Great tapas place on an UWS side street. Service is very good. Tapas were without exception delicious! They also have a nice selection of wines that match up with the variety of food nicely. Definitely a place to revisit more than once.

I was excited to try this place as it's close to my apartment and has a cute outdoor sitting area... While the decor inside is nice and people are indeed friendly, came away very disappointed for the following reasons. 1) Maybe this was an unusual experience, but the service was very very slow... Sat down ~8pm expecting to eat a quick meal and leave in 35-40 min. Instead it took us more than an 1hr 15 min, the check alone taking well over 10 min to get to us, after we asked twice. 2) Portions are very small for the price - of course it's tapas, but the sizes of some of the $12-15 dollar plates are crazy small for that price. 3) Food is pretty good but by noo means outstanding for the price.

Have enjoyed past experiences @ buceo 95 over several years but last night wasn't one of them. Our food (tortilla espanola, baked eggplant w cheese, churrasco) was definitely subpar...very disappointing! What made this Friday after work experience somewhat tolerable were the wine and music...but definitely not worth $120!!
Amazingly delicious and fairly priced Spanish tapas. The experience is very authentic compared to an upper scale tapas restaurant in Spain and the staff was wonderful. This is an upper west side gem.

Great tapas and wine. Our server was a young lady that had great attitude. The manager was also very nice and friendly. Food tasted very good but the lortions are small like Tapas normally are. If you are very hungry the tapas bill adds up fast.
Delectable tapas!  Probably some of the best in the city!  Highly recommend.. very crowded on weekends and not a quiet place

Can't say enough good about this place. I've probably had at least 50 different tapas here, although i do tend to be unable to give up long-time favorites. The staff across the board is friendly and super-competent; the wines are well-chosen for variety and distinctiveness; and the menu always introduces new dishes while holding on to many crowd-demanded favorites. In its modest way, one of the very best restaurants on the UWS, and well worth being considered a "destination" place for those outside the neighborhood.
Love it!!! The food was delicious and the service was great. Definitely will keep coming back 😍
Great food, great wine, great management and serving staff. Highly recommended

Great wine!, food,and service. It was the most Smallest place i ever see in all my life. Uncomfortable even to get a sit.  you are too close to other peoples tables and people know what are you talking.  Is not a bad place but is up to you..!   $56 for a bottle of wine or $22 for a glass of wine
Great selection of wines
Very disappointed with this restaurant. The tapas are tiny and very expensive. The quality of food was very deceiving I won't be going back there

My wife and I eat out a lot, and have been to many top rated restaurants in NYC. This is in our top 5 for New York. Incredible menu, always rotatng. Great wine list, casual-higher end feel. Good drinks, amazing food...If your considering coming here, don't hesitate!
good food and vibe. The small peppers are great!
Outstanding Tapas, a great little bar and an excellent wine selection. Cozy spot.
Great place for tapas, good wine list

Great place, lively atmosphere and very intimate. Wine selection is A1 and the staff is extremely friendly. Great place to talk to people and the food is out of this world!!! Goat cheese croquettes ftw!!
The people are friendly. The food is great. Easily the best restaurant in the neighborhood.
Charming tapas gem tucked away on the uws, great food friendly service and lively ambiance
Small and cozy, great tapas and sangria

Service was very good, not an issue here at all. Food was overpriced for what was delivered, for the costing the food needed to be perfect. Quail and eggplant tapas was good, but again questionably priced. paella was substandard, dry and little flavour. Despite this the wait staff were great, they were happy to discuss our issues with the paella and reduced the price.
Amazing tapa spot. Solid sangria.

This is a great spot. Been here twice...for brunch and dinner. On the first visit I had the duck confit...delicious! The only reason they don't get 5 stars is because I had to wait nearly an hour for it. But it was a quiet time and no big deal. Came back this evening and had traditional stuff (tortilla, gambas ajillo) and found the food, service and atmosphere to be spot on. It's as good as any quality tapas bar in Madrid or Barcelona :)
Food is amazing, service is even better it has a lot of atmosphere. If you want honest, well cooked food that isn't over the top but still delicious then go here.
Phenomenal tapas! I absolutely love this place! The food, service, and ambiance are all amazing! I highly recommend Buceo 95

Best tapas in the city. The manager is super friendly, one time they left us without menus for a few minutes and when he realized he brought us free champagne and a free dish. Excellent food with great choices and I'm always satisfied. Really good Rosé sangria.

My husband and I had dinner here tonight! Simple but yet sophisticated ambiance ! Food was reasonably priced and boy was it delicious. Service was attentive & polite. Cocktails were very different. Will definitely recommend.
Cute little tapas bar, food meets expectations. Not quite like a tapas bar in Madrid, but ok.
Awesome wine selection, knowledgeable bartenders from Spain, and authentic cuisine.
Not quite Spanish tapas, just small plates. Not the right place to understand Spanish cuisine.
A wonderful spot with a warm chic vibe Great wines by the glass and delicious food Really nice welcome by hosts/owners
amazing atmosphere with a chic neighborhood vibe great wines and wonderfully hospitable hosts/owners
Great place, good service.  Nice place for a first date, but go Mon - Weds, most other nights the place gets pretty packed.  Romantic.
Intimate setting, good little pricey dishes.
Very nice place for tapas. Great wine selection. Great service. Nice background music, nice decor and atmosphere.
Bacon wrapped dates are a must. Wine selection is great. The wait staff was so kind a helpful. The pork belly is also a must. Great place overall!!

This place is a gem. My wife disagrees, but I think it got *slightly* worse since they changed chefs, but that's personal. Either way, it's a neighborhood gem on the UWS. While the wine selection is good, you MUST have the Spicy Margarita: heavy on the cayenne pepper (just as we like it), it'll clear your sinuses then get you with a perfect lime/tequila finish.  The dishes are, well, tapas, so they're perfect for sharing two or three. The paella is the heaviest, and you'll want to share that between two with maybe 2-3 other dishes (we're fans of the duck with pear, and the blistered peppers).  When the check comes, you will be pleasantly surprised by price. For my wife and I, paella, two cocktails, and two other dishes usually comes out to about $100 with tax and tip, and we feel very satisfied and sated.

A really nice and cute place. I ordered the bison sliders which were really good. I also ordered the potato chips as an appetizer, but also got more potato chips with the sliders. They didn't charge us the appetizer's one, which was really nice. They have a really big wine menu, but I didn't try any of them. The staff was nice, and the place itself was nice but a bit crowded.

Nice atmosphere, especially inside. Large bar, lots of tall tables. The waiting staff was polite, but our waitress seemed super nervous. The tapas were OK, the quality varying a lot among the different options we tried.
Great place, nice vibe! Close together NYC seating. Highly recommend the duck!
Food was delicious and service was great. We enjoyed the pork paella.

I had a nice dinner outside last night with my wife.  This place has a surprisingly large selection of vegetarian tapas (about 15 options, or about half the menu).  Here are the dishes we ordered, best first: Ensalada Matrimonio (kale salad), Piquillos Rellenos (small cheese stuffed peppers), Tortilla Española, Coles de Bruselas (roasted brussel sprouts), and Gambas al Ajillo (shrimp in garlic sauce).  I never thought a kale salad could be so good.  Gambas al Ajillo is my wife's favorite Spanish dish and it was the only disappointment of the night.  If she had liked it, this place would have earned a five star rating.  If/when we go back, I'd happily re-order the kale salad, stuffed peppers, and the tortilla española.  The sangria was also very good.  The service was prompt, with the exception of waiting about 10 minutes to get the check.  This is NYC, people have places to be.
Delicious food and the staff was lovely, and provided great advice on their wines. I especially enjoyed their goat cheese coquettes.

This is a neighborhood gem! The service is impeccable, the best ambiance, and delicious wine selection. They serve only tapas, so it's a great place for an intimate dinner with friends or with significant other. My hubs and I come here for a glass of wine at the bar and we always end up meeting other friendly people in the UWS with the most interesting backgrounds. Every time I come here I end up staying for hours just chatting, drinking good cava or wine, and noshing on a small plate.

Restaurants like Buceo 95 make you fall in love with NY! It's an excellent neighborhood restaurant with consistently great food and friendly service. It's a perfect spot for a small-group dinner or romantic date. I've been there enough times to try practically all the dishes and you cannot really go wrong with any of them.

Buceo 95, the tapas edition to the Dive family of bars, is a neighborhood gem worth a multi-neighborhood trek and frankly serves some of the best tapas in the city. The only letdown here tends to be the speed of the service, and it's evident that one more waiter would be ideal, if only the little room could accommodate another soul without coming to a standstill. Never fear though: just catch manager Johnnie's eye (and forgive me if he spells it with a 'y') and he'll drop by to fill the gap and offer the best wine advice north of 65th Street. (Save room for sherry.)
Candlelit and cozy tapas joint with an awesome maître d’ and sommelier – they’ll remember you next time you visit. We loved the dates, lamb sliders and salt cod croquettes.
Great tapas menu.  Perfect spot before going to a concert at nearby Symphony Space.
